description:
Righteousness, a right standing before God, is not earned but credited to us—a core aspect of the doctrine of justification by faith. The video draws parallels with Abraham’s unwavering faith in God’s promise, despite its seemingly impossible fulfillment. Dive into this exploration of how, through faith in Christ, we are viewed as righteous in God's eyes, just as if we had never sinned.
